reviews.text: Not cheap. Worth every penny. Best tempura in HK.
Feel like being in Japan for great service and food😜😜
Delicious and authentic tempura. You must have both a reservation and a healthy bank account.

Perfect tempura. Believing that this is the best tempura in Hong Kong. Certainly will be back again for the best tempura. And also thanks to Chef Toyoichiro Seki for the very nice recommended sake. Salute.

Specialised tempura only restaurant.
5th generation Japanese tempura chef.
Small bench style seating for 10 people and a table for 4-6, perfect for a small gathering.
The batter is very light so even though it is all tempura it is not overpowering.
If you like tempura, worth a try

result.name: The Old Man

reviews.text:
What an awesome experience! We were five guys visiting this bar on a busy Wednesday night. It's a bit hard to find and if you go by public transport (metro) be aware that you have to walk uphill for some time. 

After arriving the friendly staff asked us to stand aside and offered us some water. We ordered a variety of different cocktails and after a few minutes we got a free table. All of the drinks were excellent, I recommend the "Torrents of Spring" which was my favourite one (strong, whiskey, masculine). 
The girls in this venue are beautifully dressed and most of the men are wearing proper shirts. The interior is cozy and interesting, only the light could be dimmed a bit more.

Thanks for making our last night in HK a great one ! Definitely coming back!

Asia's 50 Best Bars' newly crowned best bar.

It's a fairly small bar that can fit seat around 25 people. It's an Ernest Hemingway inspired bar. 

Most of the cocktails in the menu are batched due to their heavy usage of rotovaps. So drinks come out quick and service is damn good. The team is very engaging with the guests as they have more time to focus on them.

The drinks are interesting and unique. Worth going to even if just for a bit

Loved the bar and the female bartender. She was funny, made great drinks, and really took the time to talk to us! Ordered 3 drinks and one was a miss but definitely worth checking out for the atmosphere and to easily meet new people. 👌🏼

I decided to work through “Asia’s 50 Best Bars”, and no. 1 does not disappoint. This is a bar that is ALL about their cocktails. No DJ, no gimmicky decor, nothing but the drinks. There are a couple of tables, but mostly you sit at the “bar”, a long table perpendicular to the cocktail station from where you can witness each drink being assembled. Such a treat. Well done Old Man, and what a way to start my quest.

It is no wonder why The Old Man is listed as Asia's Best Bar in 2019 as well as one of the top bar in the world, the drinks were fantastic and unique. The staff and the ambiance were great! Oh and do arrive at the bar early as the place can get really crowded at night due to the limited seats.

reviews.text: The best tempura in the town, no matter lunch or dinner

reviews.author_name: l X l X k X a X
reviews.text: Wonderful Omakase lunch! Delicious tempuras with sauce recommendations by the Japanese Chief!
Simply the best tempura restaurant outside Japan and one of the top in Japan too.... Must try as Toyo San is an outstanding chef.

Wanted to try for since long time ago, luckily we were able to make a very last minute reservation on Sunday lunch, it was good value for money, they have a quite nice sake list with good price range, food were very delicious and service was good, nothing complain about it, will try dinner next time
Be warned about the price tag!  The tempura is delicious!! Personal favourite is the Uni
